&lt;p&gt;IXL Learning, developer of personalized learning products used by millions of people globally, is seeking an enthusiastic, highly motivated Associate Digital Designer to join our design team and create elegant, engaging designs and concepts across a myriad of design disciplines that will excite and motivate our audiences. This role is designed to offer new graduates or candidates with 1-2 years of experience the opportunity to quickly establish a solid understanding of our design philosophy of creating amazing edtech experiences across all of our brands: IXL, Rosetta Stone, Teachers Pay Teachers, Education.com, Wyzant, Vocabulary.com, and more.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At IXL Learning, we are dedicated to creating first-of-their-kind products that leverage cutting-edge technologies to solve seemingly intractable problems in education. Millions of users count on us to make learning as effective as can be, so we&#39;re looking for exceptional people who are committed to solving the real-world challenges faced by students and teachers around the world. Our products are renowned for making online learning both intuitive and fun, and we’re seeking an individual that can bring creative flair, innovation, and craft that will continue to delight our customers.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position requires you to be in our San Mateo, CA, headquarters office.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL BE DOING&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create visual experiences for digital/product marketing, print, user-facing web, mobile, and tablet-based platforms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Transform wireframes into original, creative mock-ups in low and high-fidelity prototypes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design brand and marketing assets that help drive engagement and support product initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inspire users with attractive, compelling designs while maintaining visual consistency and brand identity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in collaborative feedback sessions with the design team and cross-functional teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with product, marketing team members, and key stakeholders to understand and interpret project requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enhance existing interfaces or designs with new layouts, photos, graphics, and content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with our marketing teams to design emails, promotions, online ads, and marketing collateral&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;WHAT WE&#39;RE LOOKING FOR&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BA/BS degree&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience in UX/UI, product&amp;nbsp; design&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to create user-centric, clutter-free, visually consistent designs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert-level knowledge of InDesign, Illustrator, and the wider Adobe Creative Suite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to create clean, clutter-free designs that are consistent with our established style&lt;/li&gt;
